g.title: n0
g.text: Unbroken Sequence of Devon Strata
In Devon, all the strata - older than
the New Red Sandstone - form an
unbroken sequence of strata #ev #E1

g.title: n3
g.text: Unconformity in Devon
Between the Devon Culm and the
juxtaposed strata, there is at least
one formation missing from the
standard sequence #ev #E6

g.title: n6
g.text: Unconformity in Devon II
Between the main part of the Devon Culm
and its black limestone, there is at
least one formation missing from the
standard sequence #ev #E11

g.title: n1
g.text: Trough through Exmoor
There is a trough through Exmoor -
formed by a band of limestone running
out to the north coast at Ilfracombe
and south of Barnstaple #ev #E4

g.title: n2
g.text: Instances of Coal in Ancient Strata
In Munster and Pennsylvannia, there are
coal deposits in pre-Old Red Sandstone
strata #ev #E5

g.title: n4
g.text: Munster Coal as Carboniferous
In Munster, the limestone and coal
seams are pre-Carboniferous in age,
i.e there are no coal seams in pre-
Old Red Sandstone strata #ev #E8

g.title: n5
g.text: Distinct Limestones at Ilfracombe and
Barnstaple
The limestone at Ilfracombe and the
limestone south of Barnstaple are
distinct #ev #E10

g.title: n7
g.text: ML Fauna in South Devon
In south Devon, non-Culm strata fossils
are as old as the base of the Mountain
Limestone #ev #E14

g.title: n8
g.text: Non-Culm Fauna between SIL and ML
In Devon, the fossil fauna and flora of
the non-Culm strata are intermediate
in character between Silurian and
Mountain Limestone #ev #E15

g.title: n9
g.text: French Similarities
There are similarities - in fossils -
between limestones in south Devon and
northwest France #ev #E16

g.title: n20
g.text: Limestones in northwest France
In the Bocage, the limestones are as
old as the base of the Mountain
Limestone #DEV #chron-hyp

g.title: n21
g.text: South Devon and Bocage
The south Devon limestones are as old
as the limestones in the Bocage #DEV
#chron-hyp

g.title: n33
g.text: South Devon and French Limestones I
If strata can be identified by means of
their embedded fossils and the south
Devon limestones are not as old as the
limestones in the Bocage, then there
are no similarities in fossils between
them #DEV

g.title: n34
g.text: South Devon and French Limestones II
If the south Devon limestones - being
as old as the base of the Mountain
Limestone - are as old as the
limestones in the Bocage, then the
French limestones are as old as the
base of the Mountain Limestone, too
#DEV

g.title: n22
g.text: Zoological Transitions
There are true zoological transistions
all the way from the lower Cambrian to
the New Red Sandstone #DEV #pri

g.title: n36
g.text: Devon and Piecemeal Faunal Change
If there are true zoological
transitions from the Cambrian to the
New Red Sandstone and the non-Culm
strata is not intercalated between the
Silurian and Mountain Limestone, then
the fauna and flora of the non-Culm
strata are not intermediate in
character between the Silurian and the
Mountain Limestone #DEV

g.title: n35
g.text: Zoological Transitions
If there is a constant but piecemeal
faunal change, then there are true
zoological transitions from the
Cambrian to the New Red Sandstone #DEV

g.title: n23
g.text: Devonian Interpretation - DEV.1
If the Culm strata - at oldest Old Red
Sandstone in age - are juxtaposed with
Silurian and Cambrian strata, then
there is no gap in the local sequence
#DEV

g.title: n24
g.text: Devonian Interpretation - DEV.2a
If the Culm strata - being at oldest
Mountain Limestone in age - are
juxtaposed with strata ranging from
Cambrian to Old Red Sandstone, then
there is no gap in the local sequence
#DEV

g.title: n25
g.text: Devonian Interpretation - DEV.2b
If the Culm strata - at oldest Silurian
in age - are juxtaposed with strata
ranging from Cambrian to Silurian,
then there is no gap in the local
sequence #DEV

g.title: n26
g.text: Devonian Interpretation - DEV.3
If the Culm strata - being at oldest
Mountain Limestone in age - are
juxtaposed with strata intercalated
between Silurian and Mountain
Limestone strata, then there is no gap
in the local sequence #DEV

g.title: n11
g.text: Culm as ML and ORS
The Culm strata encompass the Old Red
Sandstone and the Mountain Limestone
#DEV #chron-hyp

g.title: n13
g.text: Culm as SIL, ORS, ML and CM
The Culm strata range from the upper
part of the Silurian to the Coal
Measures in age #DEV #chron-hyp

g.title: n15
g.text: Main part of the Culm as ML
In Devon, the main part of the Culm
strata is Mountain Limestone in age
#DEV #chron-hyp

g.title: n27
g.text: Extending the Sequence Downwards II -
DEV.1
If, in Devon, the main part of the Culm
strata is Mountain Limestone and their
lower part Old Red Sandstone in age,
then the Culm strata range from Old
Red Sandstone to Mountain Limestone in
age #DEV

g.title: n29
g.text: Extending the Sequence Downwards IV -
DEV.2b
If, in Devon, the main part of the Culm
strata is Coal Measures and their
lower part Mountain Limestone in age,
then the Culm strata range from
Mountain Limestone to Coal Measures
#DEV

g.title: n16
g.text: Some ML dating of Culm Limestone
Some part of the black Culm limestone
is Mountain Limestone in age #DEV
#chron-hyp

g.title: n28
g.text: Extending the Sequence Downwards III -
DEV.2b
If, in Devon, there are parts of the
black Culm limestone being upper
Silurian, Old Red Sandstone or Moutain
Limestone in age, then the Culm
Limestone ranges from upper Silurian
to Mountain Limestone #DEV

g.title: n17
g.text: Black Culm Limestone as USIL, ORS and ML
The Culm limestone ranges from the
upper part of the Silurian to the
Mountain Limestone in age #DEV
#chron-hyp

g.title: n12
g.text: Non-Culm Strata as CAM, SIL and ORS
In Devon, the non-Culm strata encompass
Cambrian, Silurian and Old Red
Sandstone strata #DEV #chron-hyp

g.title: n19
g.text: ORS and DEV as contemporanous
The Old Red Sandstone and the Devonian
non-Culm strata are contemporanous
#DEV #chron-hyp

g.title: n14
g.text: Non-Culm Strata between SIL and ML
The non-Culm strata are intercalated
between the Silurian and the Mountain
Limestone #DEV #chron-hyp

g.title: n32
g.text: DEV and ORS contemporanous
If both are intercalated between the
Silurian and Mountain Limestone, then
the Old Red Sandstone and the non-Culm
strata are contemporanous #DEV

g.title: n18
g.text: Upper ORS in South Devon
In south Devon, some limestones are as
old as the base of the Mountain
Limestone #DEV #chron-hyp

g.title: n30
g.text: ORS Non-Culm Strata in South Devon
If strata can be identified by means of
their embedded fossil and some south
Devonian non-Culm strata are not as
old as the base of the Mountain
Limestone, then there are no Mountain
Limestone fossils in south Devonian
strata #DEV

g.title: n31
g.text: Extending the Sequence Onwards IV -
DEV.2a
If, in Devon, there are some non-Culm
strata being Cambrian, Silurian or
upper Old Red Sandstone in age, then
the non-Culm strata encompasse the
Cambrian, Silurian and the whole of
the Old Red Sandstone #DEV

g.title: n10
g.text: ORS in Devon
In Devon, a significant part of strata
is equivalent to the Old Red Sandstone
#DEV #chron-hyp
